 Java library for connecting JVM and Android applications to MQTT brokers using the MQTT 5 protocol. It provides asynchronous and synchronous client APIs for publishing, subscribing, and managing MQTT messaging workflows.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/index.json:12:    \"description\": \"The jjwt-orgjson module provides JJWT's org.json-based serializer and deserializer so JWT headers and claims can be read and written using JSON-Java. It is the recommended JSON backend for Android applications and supports simple object-to-JSON marshaling instead of POJO unmarshalling.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/index.json:28:    \"description\": \"The jjwt-orgjson module provides JJWT's org.json-based serializer and deserializer so JWT claims and headers can be read and written using JSON-Java. It is the recommended JSON backend for Android applications and supports simple object-to-JSON marshaling rather than POJO unmarshalling.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/index.json:48:    \"description\": \"The jjwt-orgjson module provides JJWT's org.json-based JSON serializer and deserializer implementation for processing JWT content at runtime. It is the recommended JSON backend for Android use cases and supports simple claim marshaling without POJO unmarshalling.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-api/index.json:8:    \"description\" : \"JJWT provides APIs for creating, parsing, and verifying JSON Web Tokens and JSON Web Keys in Java and Android applications. The `jjwt-api` artifact exposes the library's public interfaces, fluent builders, and supporting types for JOSE-compliant JWT processing.\",\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-api/index.json:23:    \"description\" : \"JJWT provides APIs for creating, parsing, and verifying JSON Web Tokens and JSON Web Keys in Java and Android applications. The `jjwt-api` artifact exposes the library's stable public interfaces and fluent builders for JOSE-compliant JWT processing.\",\nmetadata/com.google.protobuf/protob